</ul>

<p>It is important to note that Heroku ended free product plans for Heroku Dynos, Heroku PostgreSQL and Heroku Data for Redis on November 28, 2022 (announced in this <a href="https://blog.heroku.com/next-chapter">Heroku blog post</a>). Even after logging back into your account, you will now need to upgrade data resources and dynos using free plans to avoid any data loss or service interruptions.</p>

<p>If you would like to keep your apps on Heroku, instructions on upgrading your apps and pricing can be found <a href="https://help.heroku.com/81MBEG7L/how-do-i-upgrade-from-heroku-s-free-tier-and-begin-using-paid-resources">here</a>. For additional information please visit our <a href="https://help.heroku.com/RSBRUH58/removal-of-heroku-free-product-plans-faq">FAQ on removal of free product plans</a> that contains information on deletion of inactive accounts and data. </p>

